# Speaker Notes Standards

Module 2 Speaker Notes is the reference. Match this format across all modules.

## Tone
- Casual conversation, like briefing Carlos in bullet points
- No long sentences, no scripts, no stage directions
- Written as "here's what we're teaching and why" — not "say this word for word"

## Structure Per Slide
- Slide number + title as H2 heading
- 2-5 bullet points covering: what's on the slide, what to say, key example
- A "Why" line explaining the pedagogical reasoning (why this exercise, what insight should land, what changes if we skip it)

## Content Rules
- Name real companies as examples, matching the slide
- Include interactive cues: "ask the room", "get 2-3 answers", "show of hands"
- Spell out acronyms on first use (ToS = Terms of Service, HITL = Human-in-the-Loop)
- If a slide has a fill-in exercise, note what "good" vs "bad" answers look like so Carlos can coach
